      "code": "{\"query\": \"lack of API access health data legal challenge lawsuit interoperability\", \"numResults\": 8, \"type\": \"deep\"}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_3628aeb81f854ca18ec72b39be385c4e\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/\",\n      \"title\": \"Health Gorilla Calls Epic Lawsuit 'Attack on Interoperability ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Mar 1, 2026 — The dispute reflects unresolved ambiguities in how data interoperability should be governed across the healthcare industry. Experts think the\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.beckershospitalreview.com/healthcare-information-technology/ehrs/health-gorilla-pushes-back-against-epic-lawsuit-over-patient-data-access/\",\n      \"title\": \"Health Gorilla pushes back against Epic lawsuit over ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Jan 27, 2026 — Health Gorilla pushes back against Epic lawsuit alleging improper patient data access through national interoperability frameworks.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ByOGyq4hgJQ\",\n      \"title\": \"Inside Epic's Massive Lawsuit\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Epic Systems has filed a lawsuit against Health Gorilla, Llama Labs, Ravila Med, and a network of other actors, alleging they exploited the\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://curanahealth.com/interoperability-api\",\n      \"title\": \"Interoperability API - Curana Health\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-04-22\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Search for:\\n\\nAbout us\\n\\nResources\\n\\n# Interoperability API\\n\\nDeveloper-friendly and secure standards-based application programming interfaces (APIs) that enable third-party application vendors to connect their applications and access Medicare Advantage data.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\n**[Interoperability and Patient Access final rule (CMS-9115-F)](https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2020/05/01/2020-05050/medicare-and-medicaid-programs-patient-protection-and-affordable-care-act-interoperability-and)** and **[the Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology's (ONC's) 21st Century Cures Act final rule (45 CFR 170.213 and 170.215)](https://www.healthit.gov/curesrule/)** support a patient's control of their health care and secure access to their electronic health records through smartphones and modern third-party software applications (“apps”).\\nPatients will be able to use “apps” of their choice and with consent, authorize and allow the “apps” to request and receive data from their Payer.  \\n  \\nIn support of the final rules, Curana Health has created the Interoperability APIs .   Curana Interoperability APIs enables client Medicare Advantage members to use “apps” of their choice to access their data. It also allows “apps” to connect to provider and pharmacy directories, further referred to as “public non-member specific data.”\\n\\nThird Party Application - Patient API Access\\n\\n## Client Medicare Advantage Payers\\n\\n|**Identification** |**Payer** |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|H1372 |AgeRight Advantage |\\n|H3274 |Align Senior Care (California) |\\n|H9917 |Align Senior Care (Florida) |\\n|H6832 |Align Senior Care (Michigan) |\\n|H6959 |KeyCare Advantage |\\n|H6566 |Lagniappe Advantage |\\n|H2185 |LifeWorks Advantage |\\n|H4172 |NHC Advantage |\\n|H3419 |Perennial Advantage (Colorado and Pennsylvania) |\\n|H8797 |Perennial Advantage (Ohio) |\\n\\n...\\n\\n## How to Contact Us for Technical Inquiries\\n\\nSend an email to [[email protected]](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection) and someone will respond to your inquiry.\\n\\nInteroperability API\\n\\nPrivacy, compliance, and terms of use\\n\\n### Derek Chao, MD\\n\\nPresident and Chief Medical Officer\\n\\nDr. Chao brings more than two decades of experience in managed care, clinical leadership, and healthcare transformation to Curana Health. Starting his medical career as a hospitalist and nephrologist in Southern California, Dr. Chao has held various leadership positions (including medical director and chief medical officer) within numerous healthcare organizations (including HealthCare Partners). Before coming to Curana, he served as chief executive officer of Optum Health’s western region, where he oversaw operations and care delivery across nine states. Dr. Chao’s expertise spans a range of healthcare models, from fee-for-service to value-based care across Medicare, Medicaid, and commercial plans.\\nHis broad experience has honed his ability to lead both clinical and operational teams through the complexities of healthcare delivery models, and his professional insights are shaped not only by his clinical expertise, but also by personal experience (having witnessed firsthand the challenges his elderly parents faced in navigating the American healthcare system). At Curana Health, Dr. Chao leads efforts to empower the organization’s healthcare providers, optimize care delivery, and ensure clinicians have the tools and support needed to achieve exceptional outcomes for patients and operator partners alike.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://curanahealth.com/interop/\",\n      \"title\": \"Interoperability API - Curana Health\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-04-22\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Search for:\\n\\nAbout us\\n\\nResources\\n\\n# Interoperability API\\n\\nDeveloper-friendly and secure standards-based application programming interfaces (APIs) that enable third-party application vendors to connect their applications and access Medicare Advantage data.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\n**[Interoperability and Patient Access final rule (CMS-9115-F)](https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2020/05/01/2020-05050/medicare-and-medicaid-programs-patient-protection-and-affordable-care-act-interoperability-and)** and **[the Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology's (ONC's) 21st Century Cures Act final rule (45 CFR 170.213 and 170.215)](https://www.healthit.gov/curesrule/)** support a patient's control of their health care and secure access to their electronic health records through smartphones and modern third-party software applications (“apps”).\\nPatients will be able to use “apps” of their choice and with consent, authorize and allow the “apps” to request and receive data from their Payer.  \\n  \\nIn support of the final rules, Curana Health has created the Interoperability APIs .   Curana Interoperability APIs enables client Medicare Advantage members to use “apps” of their choice to access their data. It also allows “apps” to connect to provider and pharmacy directories, further referred to as “public non-member specific data.”\\n\\nThird Party Application - Patient API Access\\n\\n## Client Medicare Advantage Payers\\n\\n|**Identification** |**Payer** |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|H1372 |AgeRight Advantage |\\n|H3274 |Align Senior Care (California) |\\n|H9917 |Align Senior Care (Florida) |\\n|H6832 |Align Senior Care (Michigan) |\\n|H6959 |KeyCare Advantage |\\n|H6566 |Lagniappe Advantage |\\n|H2185 |LifeWorks Advantage |\\n|H4172 |NHC Advantage |\\n|H3419 |Perennial Advantage (Colorado and Pennsylvania) |\\n|H8797 |Perennial Advantage (Ohio) |\\n\\n...\\n\\n## How to Contact Us for Technical Inquiries\\n\\nSend an email to [[email protected]](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection) and someone will respond to your inquiry.\\n\\nInteroperability API\\n\\nPrivacy, compliance, and terms of use\\n\\n### Derek Chao, MD\\n\\nPresident and Chief Medical Officer\\n\\nDr. Chao brings more than two decades of experience in managed care, clinical leadership, and healthcare transformation to Curana Health. Starting his medical career as a hospitalist and nephrologist in Southern California, Dr. Chao has held various leadership positions (including medical director and chief medical officer) within numerous healthcare organizations (including HealthCare Partners). Before coming to Curana, he served as chief executive officer of Optum Health’s western region, where he oversaw operations and care delivery across nine states. Dr. Chao’s expertise spans a range of healthcare models, from fee-for-service to value-based care across Medicare, Medicaid, and commercial plans.\\nHis broad experience has honed his ability to lead both clinical and operational teams through the complexities of healthcare delivery models, and his professional insights are shaped not only by his clinical expertise, but also by personal experience (having witnessed firsthand the challenges his elderly parents faced in navigating the American healthcare system). At Curana Health, Dr. Chao leads efforts to empower the organization’s healthcare providers, optimize care delivery, and ensure clinicians have the tools and support needed to achieve exceptional outcomes for patients and operator partners alike.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://curanahealth.com/resources/press-releases\",\n      \"title\": \"Press Releases | Curana Health | Our Latest Updates\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-01-21\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Search for:\\n\\nAbout us\\n\\nResources\\n\\n# Press releases\\n\\nRead about our latest partnerships, leadership news, and company milestones.\\n\\n[Press Releases August 18, 2025 The Piedmont at Buckhead Partners with Curana Health Read More](https://www.srgseniorliving.com/news/the-piedmont-at-buckhead-partners-with-curana-health/=ZDVjMTE4NTUtZDliMS00OTE2LTliMzktMjg3MTU3ODFjZTcz~)\\n\\n[Press Releases August 11, 2025 Cedar Community Announces Healthcare Partnership with Curana Health Read More](https://www.cedarcommunity.org/uncategorized/cedar-community-announces-healthcare-partnership-with-curana-health/)\\n\\n[Press Releases July 21, 2025 The Carlisle Naples Announces New Healthcare Partnership with Curana Health Read More](https://www.srgseniorliving.com/news/the-carlisle-naples-announces-new-healthcare-partnership-with-curana-health/=ZDVjMTE4NTUtZDli