. At Curana Health, Dr.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=cb0de270-eb65-4225-84eb-42a44aa56e84\",\n      \"title\": \"Regulators Look to Increase Interoperability and Patient Access to Health Data - Lexology\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2019-02-14\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"aspx%3fg%3dcb0de270-eb65-4225-84eb-42a44aa56e84)\\n    + [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3a%2f%2fwww.lexology.com%2flibrary%2fdetail.aspx%3fg%3dcb0de270-eb65-4225-84eb-42a44aa56e84&title=&summary=&source=)\\n    + [WhatsApp](https://api.whatsapp.com/send?text=Regulators Look to Increase Interoperability and Patient Access to Health Data - https%3a%2f%2fwww.lexology.com%2flibrary%2fdetail.aspx%3fg%3dcb0de270-eb65-4225-84eb-42a44aa56e84)\\n* Follow\\n  \\n  Please login to follow content.\\n* Like\\n* Instruct\\n\\nadd to folder:\\n\\n* My saved (default)\\n\\n### **Register now** for your free, tailored, daily legal newsfeed service.\\n\\nFind out more about Lexology or get in touch by visiting our About page.\\n\\n# Regulators Look to Increase Interoperability and Patient Access to Health Data  \\nBlog Health Care Viewpoints\\n\\nMintz\\n\\n[](http://www.mintz.com)\\n\\nUSA February 14 2019\\n\\n...\\n\\nGet closer to winning business faster with Lexology's complete suite of dynamic products designed to help you unlock new opportunities with our highly engaged audience of legal professionals looking for answers.\\n\\n[Learn more](https://go.lexology.com/lexology-engage-info)\\n\\n### Professional development\\n\\n* Mastering Data Processing Agreements - Drafting, Negotiating & Mitigating Risk- Learn Live\\n  \\n  MBL Seminars | 4 CPD hours  \\n  Online  \\n  12 May 2026\\n* Implementing & Maintaining Data Retention & Data Management Policies - Learn Live\\n  \\n  MBL Seminars | 1.5 CPD hours  \\n  Online  \\n  15 September 2026\\n\\nView all\\n\\n### Related practical resources PRO\\n\\n* How-to guide How-to guide: How to choose ethical and risk-management frameworks when drafting an AI governance policy (Global) Recently updated\\n* Checklist Checklist: Processor due diligence (data protection and cybersecurity) (EU) Recently updated\\n* Checklist Checklist: What to include in your organisation’s privacy notice (EU) Recently updated\\n\\nView all\\n\\n### Related research hubs\\n\\n#### Medicaid\\n\\n#### Google\\n\\n#### USA\\n\\n#### Healthcare & Life Sciences\\n\\n#### IT & Data Protection\\n\\n×\\n\\nClose\\n\\n## Cookie Preference Centre\\n\\n* ### Your Privacy\\n* ### Strictly Necessary Cookies\\n* ### Performance Cookies\\n* ### Functional Cookies\\n* ### Targeting Cookies\\n\\n#### Your Privacy\\n\\nWhen you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings.\\nHowever, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer.  \\n[More information](https://cookiepedia.co.uk/giving-consent-to-cookies)\\n\\n#### Strictly Necessary Cookies\\n\\nAlways Active\\n\\nThese cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.\\n\\n#### Performance Cookies\\n\\nPerformance Cookies\\n\\nThese cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/k-health-integrates-with-health-gorillas-api-to-power-lab-ordering-300896759.html\",\n      \"title\": \"K Health integrates with Health Gorilla's API to power lab ordering\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2019-08-08\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[Accessibility Statement](https://www.cision.com/about/accessibility/) Skip Navigation\\n\\n# K Health integrates with Health Gorilla's API to power lab ordering\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## News provided by\\n\\n**Health Gorilla**\\n\\nAug 08, 2019, 10:00 ET\\n\\n## Share this article\\n\\n     \\n\\nShare to X\\n\\nShare this article\\n\\n* * * * *\\n\\nShare to X\\n\\n* * *\\n\\nNEW YORK and SUNNYVALE, Calif. , Aug. 8, 2019 /PRNewswire/ -- [K Health](https://c212.net/c/link/?t=0&l=en&o=2543944-1&h=1449712116&u=http%3A%2F%2Fkhealth.ai%2F&a=K+Health) , a digital health company that offers free personalized healthcare, and [Health Gorilla](https://c212.net/c/link/?t=0&l=en&o=2543944-1&h=3200517807&u=http%3A%2F%2Fhealthgorilla.com%2F&a=Health+Gorilla) , a leader in secure interoperability solutions, announced today a collaboration to power new clinical functionality to improve the primary care experience. K Health can now leverage Health Gorilla's FHIR-based APIs to place orders with diagnostic vendors.\\n\\n...\\n\\ncom%2Fct%2FCT%3Fid%3Dsmartlink%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fitunes.apple.com%252Fus%252Fapp%252Fk-health%252Fid1180400838%253Fmt%253D8%26esheet%3D51837491%26newsitemid%3D20180717005223%26lan%3Den-US%26anchor%3DiOS%26index%3D2%26md5%3Db5c198496edfb72d2a45c27ef2fce4c4&a=iOS) and [Android](https://c212.net/c/link/?t=0&l=en&o=2543944-1&h=2470274844&u=http%3A%2F%2Fcts.businesswire.com%2Fct%2FCT%3Fid%3Dsmartlink%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fplay.google.com%252Fstore%252Fapps%252Fdetails%253Fid%253Dai.kanghealth%26esheet%3D51837491%26newsitemid%3D20180717005223%26lan%3Den-US%26anchor%3DAndroid%26index%3D3%26md5%3D2eddfe7ff8a48cba8524d775b47ec8bb&a=Android) .\\n\\n**About Health Gorilla  \\n** Founded in 2014, Health Gorilla is a secure interoperability solution that enables the entire health care ecosystem – patients, payers, providers, digital health solutions, and labs – to seamlessly share health data and aggregate each patient's entire clinical history in one place.\\n\\n...\\n\\n3 million users and is frequently the #1 most downloaded app in the App Store's medical category. K is available in all 50 states, and K Primary Care is available in 18 states, covering 200 million people. The company has raised $50M+ to date and is headquartered in New York City .\\n\\nCONTACT: Ali Zaman , [[email protected]](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection)\\n\\nSOURCE Health Gorilla\\n\\n#### Related Links\\n\\n<https://healthgorilla.com>\\n\\n[## 21 % more press release views with Request a Demo](https://www.prnewswire.com/amplify-platform/?site_refer=press-release-widget)\\n\\n×\\n\\n### Modal title\\n\\n## Also from this source\\n\\nHealth Gorilla Releases Statement in Response to Epic Lawsuit\\n\\n### Health Gorilla Releases Statement in Response to Epic Lawsuit Health Gorilla, Inc. (\\\"Health Gorilla\\\"), a leading provider of healthcare interoperability access, released a statement today in response to the...\\n\\nHealth Gorilla Named Among TIME's World's Top HealthTech Companies of 2025\\n### Health Gorilla Named Among TIME's World's Top HealthTech Companies of 2025 Health Gorilla, a leading provider of interoperability solutions and a Qualified Health Information Network (QHIN) delivering real-time,...\\n\\nMore Releases From This Source\\n\\n## Explore\\n\\nHealth Care & Hospitals\\n\\nHealth Care & Hospitals\\n\\nMedical Equipment\\n\\nMedical Equipment\\n\\nMedical Pharmaceuticals\\n\\nMedical Pharmaceuticals\\n\\nHigh Tech Security\\n\\nHigh Tech Security\\n\\nNews Releases in Similar Topics\\n\\n* Terms of Use\\n* [Privacy Policy](https://www.cision.com/legal/privacy-policy/ \\\"Privacy Policy\\\")\\n* Information Security Policy\\n* Site Map\\n* RSS\\n* Cookies\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"http://www.bswhealthplan.com/api\",\n      \"title\": \"Interoperability APIs | Baylor Scott & White Health Plan\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* **Virtual Care**\\n* [**Medical Cost Estimator**](https://my.bswhealth.com/costestimator \\\"Medical\\\")\\n* **Shop for a Plan**\\n* **Contact Us**\\n\\nInformation\\n\\n* **Pharmacy & Drugs**\\n* **Health Toolkit**\\n* **Wellness Programs**\\n* **FAQ**\\n* **About Us**\\n\\n**Find a Doctor/Pharmacy**\\n\\n# Interoperability APIs\\n\\n[Interoperability API Developer Portal](https://datastream.inovalonone.com/)\\n\\nBaylor Scott & White Health Plan (BSWHP) interoperability APIs are developer-friendly, standards-based, secure APIs that enable third-party application vendors to connect their application programs to access BSWHP data.\\n\\n* BSWHP interoperability API functionality\\n  \\n    + Enable developers to register member-facing applications\\n    + Enable members to provide consent for an application to access their data\\n    + Use the [Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources (FHIR)](https://www.hl7.org/fhir/)\\n    + Use the [OAuth 2.0 / Open ID Connect](https://oauth.\\nnet/2/) standard for member authorization using Microsoft platform.\\n* Developers portal\\n  \\n  The BSWHP [Interoperability API Developer Portal](https://developer.inovalonone.com/developer/apis/documentation/Patient%20Access%20API) provides third-party applications and payers access to documentation, registration services and developer services related to healthcare interoperability APIs provided by BSWHP, pursuant to the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services Interoperability and Patient Access Final Rule (CMS-9115-F). The patient access API will allow third-party applications to retrieve data, including but not limited to adjudicated claims, encounters and any clinical data maintained by BSWHP for both past and present members.\\n* Privacy\\n  \\n  BSWHP appreciates that your medical information is personal and we are committed to helping you understand how to protect and secure your health information. Please review our [privacy notice](https://wadcdnstorageprod.blob.core.windows.\\nnet/bswhp/Compliance-Legal/GN_Interoperability-General-BSWHP.pdf) related to interoperability and the use of third-party applications.\\n\\n## Prior authorization metrics\\n\\n##### For medical items and services (excluding drugs)\\n\\nTo comply with the CMS Interoperability and Prior Authorization [final rule](https://www.cms.gov/priorities/burden-reduction/overview/interoperability/policies-and-regulations/cms-interoperability-and-prior-authorization-final-rule-cms-0057-f/cms-interoperability-and-prior-authorization-final-rule-cms-0057-f) , Scott and White Health Plan d/b/a Baylor Scott & White Health Plan is required to annually report aggregated prior authorization metrics on our website. Specifically, this includes a list of all medical items and services (excluding drugs) that require prior authorization, as well as data on prior authorization requests for those items and services (e.g. approvals, denials, etc.) over the previous calendar year.\\n\\n...\\n\\n* For QHP issuers on the FFEs, 72 hours for expedited requests (urgent) and 15 days for standard requests (non-urgent)\\n\\nThere are no Medicaid FFS requirements regarding prior authorization decision timeframes for either type of request prior to Jan. 1, 2026, and there are no CHIP FFS requirements regarding prior authorization decision timeframes for expedited requests prior to Jan. 1, 2026.\\n\\nBeginning Jan. 1, 2026, the CMS Interoperability and Prior Authorization [final rule](https://www.cms.gov/priorities/burden-reduction/overview/interoperability/policies-and-regulations/cms-interoperability-and-prior-authorization-final-rule-cms-0057-f/cms-interoperability-and-prior-authorization-final-rule-cms-0057-f) requires Medicare Advantage plans, state Medicaid agencies, Medicaid managed care plans, state CHIP agencies and CHIP managed care entities to send prior authorization decisions within:\\n\\n* 72 hours for exp\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.mcdermottlaw.com/industries/health/digital-health\",\n      \"title\": \"Health tech & digital health law | McDermott healthcare lawyers\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-25\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"com%2Findustries%2Fhealth%2Fdigital-health%2F) [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcdermottlaw.com%2Findustries%2Fhealth%2Fdigital-health%2F) [X (Twitter)](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcdermottlaw.com%2Findustries%2Fhealth%2Fdigital-health%2F&text=Digital%20Health%20%26%23038%3B%20Health%20Tech)\\n\\nDigital Health & Health Tech\\n\\nDecorative graphic\\n\\nOverview\\n\\n## Digital health legal solutions\\n\\nDigital health solutions are fundamentally transforming the quality and delivery of healthcare. As the doctor-patient relationship evolves beyond the in-person encounter, digitized data and technology have converged with healthcare delivery and payment. Our digital health team works with clients to create solutions that improve access to medical services and engage patients in managing their healthcare, with an eye toward the complex and ever-evolving regulatory considerations affecting healthcare innovation.\\n\\nSee More\\nLarge and impressively versatile team offers well-honed expertise in all areas of healthcare law, including data privacy matters… Experience includes large-scale telehealth mandates and restructuring concerns.\\n\\n_Chambers USA_\\n\\nUpcoming events\\n\\nOur events provide exciting networking opportunities and unique programming that offer insight into the healthcare and life sciences industries. These events are attended by leading providers, investors, founders, and other senior leaders.\\n\\nInformation Blocking and Interoperability in Healthcare Rules and Resources\\n\\nStay ahead of changing regulatory requirements and legal and policy developments impacting information blocking and interoperability in healthcare.\\n\\nAI in Healthcare Law Center\\n\\nWe continue to closely monitor the state of AI in healthcare to help you maximize the value of data and AI with an eye toward compliance in this rapidly evolving regulatory landscape.\\n\\nResults\\n* LetsGetChecked, a leading global healthcare solutions company, in its acquisition of Truepill, a leading digital pharmacy platform\\n* Eir Partners Capital, a Miami-based private equity firm, and its portfolio company, GiftHealth, Inc., a leading healthcare technology platform simplifying the prescription drug process for patients, providers, and pharmaceutical manufacturers, in its acquisition of Occam Health Services, LLC, a healthcare technology company providing patient access solutions for the pharmaceutical industry\\n* Numerous clients with platforms related to weight loss, food intake and exercise in the development of national weight-loss programs that leverage Glucagon-like peptide-1 (GLP-1) and other innovative medication treatment plans, such as personal coaching and compounded medications\\n\\nSee More\\n\\nInsights\\n\\n[FDA takes aim at misleading online claims for compounded GLP-1 drugs](https://www.mcdermottlaw.\\n\\n...\\n\\ncom/insights/character-flaw-pennsylvanias-crackdown-on-ai-playing-doctor/)\\n\\n[View All](https://www.mcdermottlaw.com/insights/?rel=712)\\n\\nEvents\\n\\n[McDermott HealthEx 2027](https://www.mcdermottlaw.com/events/mcdermott-healthex-2027/)\\n\\nIn-person\\n\\n[McDermott HealthEx 2027](https://www.mcdermottlaw.com/events/mcdermott-healthex-2027/)\\n\\n[Data De-Identification in Complex Data Sharing Arrangements: How AI, MNPI Considerations, and Innovative Downstream Data Models Are Changing De-Identification Strategies](https://www.mcdermottlaw.com/events/data-de-identification-in-complex-data-sharing-arrangements-how-ai-mnpi-considerations-and-innovative-downstream-data-models-are-changing-de-identification-strategies/)\\n\\nVirtual\\n\\n[Data De-Identification in Complex Data Sharing Arrangements: How AI, MNPI Considerations, and Innovative Downstream Data Models Are Changing De-Identification Strategies](https://www.mcdermottlaw.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0cba093c2ffeCsX4cK31TWSMpy\"\n}",
