      "output": "             Health Gorilla Calls Epic Lawsuit ‘Attack on Interoperability’ in Motion to Dismiss - MedCity News                                           \n\n-   [Twitter](https://twitter.com/medcitynews)\n-   [Facebook](https://facebook.com/medcitynews)\n-   [TikTok](https://www.tiktok.com/@medcity_news)\n-   [YouTube](https://youtube.com/@medcitynews)\n-   [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/medcity-news/)\n-   [RSS](/feed/)\n-   [Subscribe via email](/subscribe/)\n\n-   [Newsletter Signup](https://medcitynews.com/subscribe/)\n-   [Send Tips](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#fd89948d8ebd9098999e94898493988a8ed39e9290)\n-   [Webinars](https://medcitynews.com/tag/webinars/)\n-   [eBooks](https://hub.medcitynews.com/)\n\nOpen navigation\n\n[MedCity News](https://medcitynews.com/)\n\nToggle Search\n\nClose navigation\n\n-   [News](https://medcitynews.com/category/news/?utm_source=mn-1)\n    -   [Health Tech](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/health-tech/?utm_source=mn-1)\n    -   [BioPharma](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/biopharma/?utm_source=mn-1)\n    -   [Devices & Diagnostics](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/medical-devices-and-diagnostics/?utm_source=mn-1)\n    -   [Consumer / Employer](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/consumer-employer/?utm_source=mn-1)\n-   [Contributors](https://medcitynews.com/category/medcity-influencers/?utm_source=mn-1)\n    -   [MedCity Influencers](https://medcitynews.com/category/medcity-influencers/?utm_source=mn-1)\n-   Events\n    -   [Bullseye](https://bullseye.medcitynews.com/)\n    -   [INVEST Digital Health](https://medcityinvestconference.com/digitalhealth)\n-   [Podcasts](https://medcitynews.com/medcity-podcasts/)\n-   [Research](https://hub.medcitynews.com/)\n-   [Spotlight](https://medcitynews.com/tag/spotlight-payer-challenges-and-opportunities/)\n    -   [Payer Challenges and Opportunities](https://medcitynews.com/tag/spotlight-payer-challenges-and-opportunities/)\n-   [Newsletters](https://medcitynews.com/subscribe/)\n\n-   [Newsletter Signup](https://medcitynews.com/subscribe/)\n-   [Send Tips](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#493d20393a09242c2d2a203d30272c3e3a672a2624)\n-   [Webinars](https://medcitynews.com/tag/webinars/)\n-   [eBooks](https://hub.medcitynews.com/)\n\n-   [Twitter](https://twitter.com/medcitynews)\n-   [Facebook](https://facebook.com/medcitynews)\n-   [TikTok](https://www.tiktok.com/@medcity_news)\n-   [YouTube](https://youtube.com/@medcitynews)\n-   [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/medcity-news/)\n-   [RSS](/feed/)\n-   [Subscribe via email](/subscribe/)\n\n Search for:  Search\n\n[Health Tech,](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/health-tech/) [Startups,](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/startup-channel/) [Providers](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/providers/)\n\n# Health Gorilla Calls Epic Lawsuit ‘Attack on Interoperability’ in Motion to Dismiss\n\nHealth data company Health Gorilla filed a motion to dismiss a lawsuit from Epic and several healthcare providers alleging inappropriate access to nearly 300,000 patient records. The case highlights ongoing questions about governance and standards for national health data sharing, with Health Gorilla arguing the dispute should be handled through interoperability networks’ internal processes rather than in federal court.\n\nBy [Katie Adams](https://medcitynews.com/author/kadams/) on March 01, 2026 6:20 pm\n\n**Share**\n\n**Share Options**\n\nShare a link to this article\n\n-   Copy Link Copy Link\n-   [Email](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#83bce1ece7fabeebf7f7f3f0b9acaceee6e7e0eaf7faede6f4f0ade0eceeacb1b3b1b5acb3b0acebe6e2eff7ebaee4ecf1eaefefe2aee6f3eae0aee7e2f7e2aeeaedf7e6f1ecf3e6f1e2e1eaefeaf7faac)\n-   [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n-   [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/cws/share?url=https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n-   [X](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n\n![Corruption in the judiciary, the judge's gavel and euro banknotes in an envelope. Representation of corruption and bribery in the judiciary.](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/03/court.jpg)\n\nHealth data network [Health Gorilla](https://medcitynews.com/tag/health-gorilla/) has filed a motion to dismiss a lawsuit brought earlier this year by [Epic](https://medcitynews.com/tag/epic/) and several health systems alleging improper access to patient records. \n\n[The motion](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/62719a041d28d7b5603dd995/69a0632f55ccce3651feff55_HG%27s%20Memo%20ISO%20MTD%20C.D.%20Cal.%2026-cv-00321%20dckt%2056_001%202026-02-26.pdf), filed last Thursday, called Epic’s lawsuit “an attack on interoperability.”\n\nThe dispute reflects unresolved ambiguities in how data interoperability should be governed across the healthcare industry. [Experts think](https://medcitynews.com/2026/01/epic-health-gorilla-lawsuit-interoperability-data/) the lawsuit is less about stopping one bad actor — and more about the need to define standardized rules and boundaries around healthcare data exchange. \n\npresented by\n\n![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2025/04/veradigm-logo-2023.png)\n\n[Sponsored Post](https://medcitynews.com/category/sponsored-post/)\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/05/Veradigm_women_sreport_thumb_wordpress-360x200.jpg)](https://info.medcitynews.com/the-power-of-real-world-data-to-study-womens-health-at-scale)\n\n### [The Power of Real World Data to Study Women’s Health at Scale](https://info.medcitynews.com/the-power-of-real-world-data-to-study-womens-health-at-scale)\n\nVeradigm examines key clinical trends, comorbidity profiles, and treatment trends across adolescence, reproductive years, and peri-/post-menopause. Download it today!\n\n[By Veradigm and MedCity News](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n\n[Epic’s complaint](https://www.epic.com/content/what-you-put-up-with-is-what-you-stand-for.pdf), filed January 13, claims that Health Gorilla enabled other companies to inappropriately access and monetize nearly 300,000 patient medical records. Health Gorilla has denied the allegations.\n\nThe plaintiffs are Epic, [Trinity Health](https://medcitynews.com/tag/Trinity-Health/), [UMass Memorial Health](https://www.ummhealth.org/), [Reid Health](https://medcitynews.com/tag/reid-health/) and [OCHIN](https://ochin.org/). They allege that Health Gorilla and a network of other companies set up fictitious healthcare providers, shell websites and fake provider IDs to make it look like records requests were for real treatment purposes. Instead, the data was allegedly diverted for non-treatment uses — such as marketing to lawyers seeking potential claimants for lawsuits.\n\nThe other companies involved in the network are a cluster of small telehealth, data and shell companies — many allegedly linked to the same founders and operators — that the plaintiffs say were used to pose as legitimate providers.\n\nThe complaint also stated that the defendants inserted “junk” information into records to hide their activity and give the appearance of genuine care, which in turn risked patient safety and wasted clinician time. When one fraudulent entity was exposed, the same actors allegedly created new companies to continue the same conduct, operating “like a Hydra,” according to the lawsuit.\n\npresented by\n\n![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/05/RGB-verato-logo-R-800px-wide-4.png)\n\n[Sponsored Post](https://medcitynews.com/category/sponsored-post/)\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/06/GettyImages-2226074175-360x200.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/06/the-payer-ai-readiness-gap-why-better-data-will-define-the-next-era-of-health-plan-performance/)\n\n### [New Webinar: The Payer AI Readiness Gap: Why Better Data Will Define the Next Era of Health Plan Performance](https://medcitynews.com/2026/06/the-payer-ai-readiness-gap-why-better-data-will-define-the-next-era-of-health-plan-performance/)\n\nWe'll explore why the next era of payer performance will depend on building a trusted data foundation that connects people, providers, and relationships across the enterprise.\n\n[By Verato and MedCity News](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n\nIn its motion to throw out the case, Health Gorilla argued that the dispute should be handled through the networks’ built-in governance and dispute resolution processes rather than federal litigation. \n\nThe company also said it cooperated with months-long investigations into the issue, and it maintains that Epic’s lawsuit threatens the stability of national data sharing systems used by providers.\n\n“Epic tries to paint itself as a good actor because it has come under sustained criticism and inquiry from regulators and private plaintiffs for its widespread unfair business practices, and it desperately needs a distraction from its primary goals, which are to continue enriching itself at the expense of patients nationwide. The case should be dismissed,” Health Gorilla’s motion stated.\n\nThe Health Gorilla lawsuit is the latest in a series of legal disputes for Epic, which is also locked in a high-profile battle with data platform [Particle Health](https://medcitynews.com/tag/particle-health/). \n\nIn September 2024, Particle Health [sued](https://medcitynews.com/2024/09/epic-ehr-healthcare-lawsuit-data/) Epic over claims that the EHR vendor is using its dominance in the market to prevent competition in the payer platform space. The complaint claims that Epic imposed technical and contractual barriers that limited access to patient data, which has effectively blocked rivals from building competing payer-facing platforms. Last September, a federal judge [advanced](https://medcitynews.com/2025/09/epic-particle-data-healthcare-monopoly-capitalism/) the antitrust lawsuit. \n\nEpic is fighting vigorously in both lawsuits.\n\n“Medical records are deeply personal and exploiting them is wrong. In their motion, Health Gorilla asserts that they should be dismissed as a defendant in the lawsuit because they had ‘lack of actual knowledge’ of wrongdoing. That is not an acceptable reason — Health Gorilla had a responsibility to safeguard sensitive patient data and know why it was being taken,” an Epic spokesperson said in a statement sent to *MedCity News*.\n\nThe EHR giant added that the public deserves a complete investigation and resolution in federal court rather than behind closed doors.\n\n*Photo: SimpleImages, Getty Images*\n\n## Topics:\n\n-   [data exchange](https://medcitynews.com/tag/data-exchange/ )\n-   [data interoperability](https://medcitynews.com/tag/data-interoperability/ )\n-   [data network](https://medcitynews.com/tag/data-network/ )\n-   [Epic](https://medcitynews.com/tag/epic/ )\n-   [Health Gorilla](https://medcitynews.com/tag/health-gorilla/ )\n-   [interoperability](https://medcitynews.com/tag/interoperability/ )\n-   [lawsuit](https://medcitynews.com/tag/lawsuit/ )\n\n## More from MedCity News\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2020/10/Jackie-Niam-lungs-getty-images-e1602021314401.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/celea-lung-idiopathic-pulmonary-fibrosis-puretech-ipf-startup-deupirfenidone/)\n\n### [Lung-Focused Celea Secures $180M for Pivotal Test of Pulmonary Fibrosis Drug](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/celea-lung-idiopathic-pulmonary-fibrosis-puretech-ipf-startup-deupirfenidone/)\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2021/04/GettyImages-1050186636.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/modernizing-program-integrity-in-medicaid-self-directed-care/)\n\n### [Modernizing Program Integrity in Medicaid Self-Directed Care](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/modernizing-program-integrity-in-medicaid-self-directed-care/)\n\n[![virtual therapy psychiatry mental health](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2021/08/Teletherapy-.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/ai-in-mental-health-why-clinicians-need-to-be-in-the-room/)\n\n### [AI in Mental Health: Why Clinicians Need to Be in the Room](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/ai-in-mental-health-why-clinicians-need-to-be-in-the-room/)\n\n[![Wooden Jigsaw Puzzle About to Be Finished With a Blank Area Close-up Full Frame View.](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/03/failure-360x200.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/when-evidence-gap-becomes-a-commercial-liability/)\n\n### [When Evidence Gap Becomes a Commercial Liability](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/when-evidence-gap-becomes-a-commercial-liability/)\n\n## From the MedCity News Network\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/03/vonecia-carswell-0aMMMUjiiEQ-unsplash-360x200.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/top-fertility-supplements-for-women-in-the-u-s-what-to-know/)\n\n### [Top Fertility Supplements for Women in the U.S.: What to Know](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/top-fertility-supplements-for-women-in-the-u-s-what-to-know/)\n\nOvaterra\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/03/GettyImages-1359297865-360x200.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/survey-on-the-healthcare-financial-landscape-offers-a-roadmap-for-stakeholders/)\n\n### [Healthcare Finance Survey Offers Key Roadmap](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/survey-on-the-healthcare-financial-landscape-offers-a-roadmap-for-stakeholders/)\n\nZelis\n\n[![Health Tech Vendor Due Diligence: A HIPAA Security Guide for Medical Practices](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/01/GettyImages-837101376-360x200.jpg)](https://info.medcitynews.com/health-tech-vendor-due-diligence-a-hipaa-security-guide-for-medical-practices)\n\n### [How to Evaluate Health Tech Vendors for HIPAA Compliance and Data Security](https://info.medcitynews.com/health-tech-vendor-due-diligence-a-hipaa-security-guide-for-medical-practices)\n\nRingCentral\n\n[![Using Real World Data from the Patient Experience to Improve Drug Development](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/02/GettyImages-1170092264-360x200.jpg)](https://info.medcitynews.com/using-real-world-data-from-the-patient-experience-to-improve-drug-development)\n\n### [Putting Patients First: Using RWD to Improve Drug Discovery and Outcomes](https://info.medcitynews.com/using-real-world-data-from-the-patient-experience-to-improve-drug-development)\n\nPurpleLab\n\n[![hospitals and health systems](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2025/10/mccn_article_thuimb-360x200.png)](https://info.medcitynews.com/hancock-healths-1.1m-turnaround)\n\n### [Hancock Health’s Patient Retention Plan Delivers $1.1M in Financial Gains](https://info.medcitynews.com/hancock-healths-1.1m-turnaround)\n\nMayo Clinic Platform\n\n[![Top-Rated Health Insurance Plans for Companies With Remote Employees](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/02/fidsor-insurance-7065113_1280-360x200.png)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/02/top-rated-health-insurance-plans-for-companies-with-remote-employees/)\n\n### [Top-Rated Health Insurance Plans for Companies With Remote Employees](https://medcitynews.com/2026/02/top-rated-health-insurance-plans-for-companies-with-remote-employees/)\n\nThe Difference Card\n\n[![Nurse providing care and advice to a patient in a hospital setting](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2025/11/patient-care-576x320.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/inside-an-automated-healthcare-practice-redesigning-care-around-people-not-paperwork/)\n\n[Sponsored Post](https://medcitynews.com/category/sponsored-post/)\n\n### [Inside an Automated Healthcare Practice: Redesigning Care Around People, Not Paperwork](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/inside-an-automated-healthcare-practice-redesigning-care-around-people-not-paperwork/) \n\nBy reducing administrative burden and redesigning workflows around human needs, it creates space for what matters most: connection between clinicians and patients.\n\n[By Michael Blackman, MD, MBA Chief Medical Officer, Greenway Health®](https://bit.ly/4bHLuqy)\n\n## Recommended\n\n[BioPharma,](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/biopharma/) [Startups](https://medcitynews.com/category/channel/startup-channel/)\n\n### [Lung-Focused Celea Secures $180M for Pivotal Test of Pulmonary Fibrosis Drug](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/celea-lung-idiopathic-pulmonary-fibrosis-puretech-ipf-startup-deupirfenidone/)\n\n[MedCity Influencers](https://medcitynews.com/category/medcity-influencers/)\n\n### [Modernizing Program Integrity in Medicaid Self-Directed Care](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/modernizing-program-integrity-in-medicaid-self-directed-care/)\n\n[MedCity Influencers](https://medcitynews.com/category/medcity-influencers/)\n\n### [AI in Mental Health: Why Clinicians Need to Be in the Room](https://medcitynews.com/2026/07/ai-in-mental-health-why-clinicians-need-to-be-in-the-room/)\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/04/Gemini_Generated_Image_gnokehgnokehgnok-576x320.png)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/05/top-7-modern-ai-powered-eap-providers-for-global-workforces-in-2026/)\n\n[Sponsored Post](https://medcitynews.com/category/sponsored-post/)\n\n### [Top 7 Modern AI-Powered EAP Providers for Global Workforces in 2026](https://medcitynews.com/2026/05/top-7-modern-ai-powered-eap-providers-for-global-workforces-in-2026/)\n\nDiscover the top AI-powered EAP providers for 2026. Compare platforms like Kyan Health and Spring Health on triage speed, global reach, and clinical quality to transform workforce wellbeing.\n\n[By Tiffany Cabasso, Operations Director, Kyan Health | Psychologist, FSP](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n\n[![](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2026/06/MedCity-News-Image-for-HC-Article-576x320.jpg)](https://medcitynews.com/2026/06/the-healthcare-payments-industry-has-a-perception-problem/)\n\n[Sponsored Post](https://medcitynews.com/category/sponsored-post/)\n\n### [The Healthcare Payments Industry Has a Perception Problem](https://medcitynews.com/2026/06/the-healthcare-payments-industry-has-a-perception-problem/)\n\nHealthcare payments are no longer about transactions. It’s about controlling the revenue cycle. And increasingly, that control is not sitting with ISOs.\n\n[By Lisa Brooks, Vice President, Healthcare Partnerships](https://medcitynews.com/2026/03/health-gorilla-epic-data-interoperability/)\n\n-   [Advertise](https://medcitynews.com/ads/)\n-   [About](https://medcitynews.com/about-us/)\n-   [Newsletter](https://medcitynews.com/subscribe/)\n\n## Our Sites\n\n[![Above the Law](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/themes/breakingmedia/dist//images/above-the-law.webp)](https://abovethelaw.com/)\n\n[![How Appealing](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/themes/breakingmedia/dist//images/logo-how-appealing.webp)](https://howappealing.abovethelaw.com/)\n\n[![Breaking Defense](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/themes/breakingmedia/dist//images/breaking-defense.webp)](https://breakingdefense.com/)\n\n[![Deal Breaker](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/themes/breakingmedia/dist//images/dealbreaker.webp)](https://dealbreaker.com/)\n\n[![Fashionista](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/themes/breakingmedia/dist//images/fashionista-logo.webp)](https://fashionista.com/)\n\n[![Med City News](https://medcitynews.com/wp-content/themes/breakingmedia/dist//images/medcity-news.webp)](https://medcitynews.com/)\n\n© 2026 Breaking Media, Inc. All rights reserved. Registration or use of this site constitutes acceptance of our [Terms of Service](https://medcitynews.com/medcitizen-terms-of-service/) and [Privacy Policy](https://medcitynews.com/privacy-policy/).\n\n[![DMCA compliant image](https://www.dmca.com/img/Compliance-Trace-White.svg)](https://www.dmca.com/compliance/abovethelaw.com \"DMCA Compliance information for abovethelaw.com\")\n\n      \n\n  \n\n×",
